  "body": "This is an improvement/change request.\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n`sharedIndexInformer.Run(stopCh <-chan struct{})` (k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/shared_informer.go) calls `sharedProcessor.run()` and `controller.Run()` which spawn 2 goroutines for each attached listener and 1 goroutine. When `stopCh` is closed, `sharedIndexInformer.Run` returns, not waiting for all goroutines to finish.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nIt'd be great if `SharedInformer.Run()` method waited for all goroutines to finish.\r\nCurrently it is hard to write deterministic tests and code that dynamically starts/stops informers and adds listeners.\r\n\r\np.s. Also there is a slight inconsistency in naming - for example `Reflector.Run` / `RunUntil`, `sharedProcessor.run()` start goroutines and return, while other `Run` methods block. Would be great to have `Start` methods that start goroutines (like e.g. informer factories) and return and `Run` methods that block.",
